OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FEx-minister pressed on     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FCovid plan for disabled    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fpeople                     
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, An ex-minister has defended the        
OL,6, government's approach to disabled      
OL,7, people during the pandemic, following  
OL,8, claims they were "largely disregarded".
OL,10,FJustin Tomlinson, a former minister for
OL,11,Fdisabled people, told the Covid inquiry
OL,12,Fthe government recognised this group   
OL,13,Fwas at greater risk from the virus.    
OL,15,FHe added that work had been done "at   
OL,16,Fpace" to address this.                 
OL,18,FThe inquiry has previously been told   
OL,19,Fthat disabled people's views were not  
OL,20,Fproperly heard ahead of key decisions. 
